Now, time to standardize the data. Two dataframes will be used that is prepared above: all_pc(all patient and controls) and nogen_pc(no genetic data containing patient and control data). In both the columns that has 1 and 2 null values replaced with mean of the column.

First will analyze without genetic data. Then the genetic data will be hot encoded to mark the variations exist or not exist so that they can be numeric values as well.

In [24]:
# all_pc.info()
In [25]:
#split data to training and test sets
def preprocess_inputs(data):
    data = data.copy()
    
    #Rename target values
    data['Group'] = data['Group'].replace({
        1: "Patient",
        2: "Control"
    })
    
    # Split data into X and y
    y = data["Group"]
    X = data.drop("Group", axis=1)
    
    #Train-test split
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, train_size=0.7, shuffle=True, random_state=42)
    
    #Scale X
    scaler = StandardScaler()
    scaler.fit(X_train)
    X_train = pd.DataFrame(scaler.transform(X_train), index=X_train.index, columns=X_train.columns)
    X_test = pd.DataFrame(scaler.transform(X_test), index=X_test.index, columns=X_test.columns)
    
    
    return  X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test

# filter all the lists based on the patient list in the data trained that has genetic info
demographics_filtered = demographics[demographics["PATNO"].isin(patno_all)]
age_filtered = age[age["PATNO"].isin(patno_all)]
part_stat_filtered = part_status[part_status["PATNO"].isin(patno_all)]
family_hist_filtered = family_hist[family_hist["PATNO"].isin(patno_all)]

# inspect and clean up the null values
demog_null = demographics_filtered.isnull().sum()
age_null = age_filtered.isnull().sum()
part_null = part_stat_filtered.isnull().sum()
family_null = family_hist_filtered.isnull().sum()

demog_null = demog_null[demog_null > 0].index.tolist()
age_null = age_null[age_null > 0].index.tolist()
part_null = part_null[part_null > 0].index.tolist()
family_null =  family_null[family_null > 0].index.tolist()

demog_info = demographics_filtered.loc[:, ~demographics_filtered.columns.isin(demog_null)]
age_info = age_filtered.loc[:, ~age_filtered.columns.isin(age_null)]
participant_info = part_stat_filtered.loc[:, ~part_stat_filtered.columns.isin(part_null)]
family_info = family_hist_filtered.loc[:, ~family_hist_filtered.columns.isin(family_null)]

# merge them on the PATNO, removed the duplicate columns
diff1 = demog_info.columns.difference(age_info.columns)
diff2 = family_info.columns.difference(participant_info.columns)

data1 = demog_info[diff1]
data2 = family_info[diff2]

df_merged1 = pd.merge(age_info, data1, left_index=True, right_index=True, how='inner')
df_merged2 = pd.merge(participant_info, data2, left_index=True, right_index=True, how='inner')


diff3= df_merged1.columns.difference(df_merged2.columns)
data3 = df_merged1[diff3]

demographics = pd.merge(df_merged2, data3, left_index=True, right_index=True, how='inner')

for i, column in enumerate(demog_norace.columns):
    sns.histplot(data=demog_norace[column], ax=axs[i])
    axs[i].set_title(column, fontsize=14)
    axs[i].set_xlabel('')
    axs[i].set_ylabel('Count', fontsize=12)
    axs[i].tick_params(labelsize=12)
    
    axs[i].tick_params(axis='x', labelrotation=45)



# Remove unused subplots from the figure
for i in range(len(demog_norace.columns), nrows*ncols):
    fig.delaxes(axs[i])


# Adjust the spacing between the subplots
plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=1, hspace=1)

# Show the figure
plt.show()
